{#
    standard/user/register_form_theme.html.twig

    Symfony Twig form theme applied ONLY to the /register form via:
        {% form_theme form '@ezdesign/user/register_form_theme.html.twig' %}
    in templates/themes/standard/user/register.html.twig.

    ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    WHY THIS FILE EXISTS — DUPLICATE LABEL ROOT CAUSES
    ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    The register form uses UserRegisterType (extends BaseContentType) which
    renders a FieldCollectionType of ContentFieldType entries. This produces
    two label renders per field:

    SOURCE A — the OUTER (duplicate, unwanted) label:
        Each ContentFieldType entry is keyed by field identifier in
        FieldCollectionType::buildForm() (PRE_SET_DATA listener):
            vendor/se7enxweb/ezplatform-content-forms/
                src/lib/Form/Type/Content/FieldCollectionType.php
        The key ('first_name', 'last_name', 'user_account' …) is humanised by
        Symfony's LabelGuesser → "First name", "Last name", "User account" …
        Symfony's default form_row then renders a <label> for this outer row.
        → This is the FIRST occurrence of the label. WE SUPPRESS IT HERE.

    SOURCE B — the INNER (wanted) label:
        Each field type mapper explicitly passes:
            'label' => $fieldDefinition->getName()
        e.g. for text fields:
            vendor/se7enxweb/ezplatform-content-forms/
                src/lib/FieldType/Mapper/TextLineFormMapper.php  (line ~35)
        Equivalent mappers exist for every field type (ezuser, eztext, ezimage …)
        in the same Mapper/ directory.
        → This is the SECOND (correct) occurrence. WE KEEP IT.

    SOURCE C — the "Fields" collection heading:
        The fieldsData FieldCollectionType is added with:
            'label' => 'ezplatform.content_forms.content.fields'
        in BaseContentType::buildForm():
            vendor/se7enxweb/ezplatform-content-forms/
                src/lib/Form/Type/Content/BaseContentType.php  (line 43)
        Symfony's form_row renders this as a <label> wrapping the whole
        collection → "Fields" heading above all inputs.
        → WE SUPPRESS IT in register.html.twig by calling form_widget(form.fieldsData)
          directly (skipping form_row) which never emits the collection label.

    ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    BLOCK NAMES (Symfony convention: blockPrefix + "_row" / "_widget" etc.)
    ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    ContentFieldType::getBlockPrefix() → 'ezplatform_content_forms_content_field'
        → row block:    ezplatform_content_forms_content_field_row   ← overridden below
        → widget block: ezplatform_content_forms_content_field_widget

    FieldCollectionType (extends CollectionType, no getBlockPrefix override)
        → block prefix derived from class name: 'field_collection'
        → row block: field_collection_row (not overridden; suppressed via template)

    ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}

{#
    ── OVERRIDE: ezplatform_content_forms_content_field_row ────────────────────
    Suppresses SOURCE A (the outer duplicate label).
    Default form_row renders: form_label + form_widget + form_errors.
    We render: form_widget + form_errors only.
    The form_widget on a ContentFieldType entry expands to its compound children
    (the 'value' sub-field added by the field mapper) which carry SOURCE B labels.
#}
{% block ezplatform_content_forms_content_field_row %}
    {#- No form_label here — outer label would duplicate the inner one from the mapper. -#}
    {{- form_widget(form) -}}
    {{- form_errors(form) -}}
{% endblock %}

{#
    ── OVERRIDE: ezplatform_fieldtype_ezuser_row ────────────────────────────────
    Suppresses the "User account" section heading.

    SOURCE: UserAccountFieldValueFormMapper::mapFieldValueForm() line ~50
        vendor/se7enxweb/ezplatform-content-forms/
            src/lib/FieldType/Mapper/UserAccountFieldValueFormMapper.php
        Sets 'label' => $fieldDefinition->getName() on the 'value' sub-field
        of type UserAccountFieldType (block prefix: ezplatform_fieldtype_ezuser).
    Symfony renders this compound type's label as a visible heading above the
    username/password/email inputs — "User account" in English.
    We skip form_label and render only the widget (which contains the actual
    username, password, email sub-fields) and any errors.
#}
{% block ezplatform_fieldtype_ezuser_row %}
    {#- "User account" heading suppressed — see comment above this block. -#}
    {{- form_widget(form) -}}
    {{- form_errors(form) -}}
{% endblock %}

{#
    ── OVERRIDE: ezplatform_fieldtype_ezimage_widget ────────────────────────────
    Moves the "Remove" checkbox to below the "Alternative text" input.

    DEFAULT ORDER (from BinaryBaseFieldType + ImageFieldType::buildForm()):
        1. remove       (CheckboxType)   ← BinaryBaseFieldType.php ~line 42
        2. file         (FileType)       ← BinaryBaseFieldType.php ~line 50
        3. alternativeText (TextType)    ← ImageFieldType.php ~line 42
        4. additionalData  (JsonArrayType)   hidden

    VENDOR FILES:
        vendor/se7enxweb/ezplatform-content-forms/
            src/lib/Form/Type/FieldType/BinaryBaseFieldType.php
            src/lib/Form/Type/FieldType/ImageFieldType.php

    We reorder to: file → alternativeText → remove, hiding additionalData.
#}
{% block ezplatform_fieldtype_ezimage_widget %}
    {#- file upload input -#}
    {{- form_row(form.file) -}}
    {#- alternative text input (label from ImageFieldType.php ~line 46: "Alternative text") -#}
    {{- form_row(form.alternativeText) -}}
    {#- "Remove" checkbox placed last, below alt text -#}
    {{- form_row(form.remove) -}}
    {#- additionalData is a hidden JsonArrayType — rendered silently via form_rest -#}
    {{- form_rest(form) -}}
{% endblock %}
